<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1292,1878]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[264,487,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Material examined</emphasis>
: Lorestan Province, stream 
<quantity box="[821,896,1292,1318]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="km" value="20.0">20 km</quantity>
from spring area Abe Sarabe Sefid, 
<date box="[264,399,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1977-09-24">
<number box="[264,335,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="24.09">24.09</number>
. 
<number box="[339,399,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</date>
, leg. Schwoerbel &amp; Sepasgosarian (
<number box="[821,837,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[846,861,1332,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
/0).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1292,1878]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
In view of small dimensions, a rather short medial suture line of Cx­ 
<number box="[1140,1155,1372,1398]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<quantity box="[1171,1216,1372,1398]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
males, a realtively long P­ 
<number box="[472,482,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number box="[497,616,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="14.2" valueMax="14.3" valueMin="14.1">14.1–14.3</number>
% total length), distal margins of P­ 
<number box="[1041,1055,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
and P­ 
<number box="[1140,1153,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
without denticles, and the absence of an elogated ventral seta on P­ 
<number box="[893,908,1452,1478]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.0">4</number>
, the Iranian specimens show a general conformity with the variability range of the 
<typeStatus box="[838,889,1492,1518]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
series and of Sicilian populations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Di Sabatino et al. 1992" authorityName="Di Sabatino et al." authorityYear="1992" box="[264,901,1532,1558]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lusitanicus">
<emphasis box="[264,575,1532,1557]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Monatractides lusitanicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[595,892,1532,1558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="8" refString="Di Sabatino, A., Gerecke, R. &amp; Cicolani, B. (1992) The water mites of the family Torrenticolidae Piersig, 1902 (Acari, Actinedida) in springs and running waters of Sicily (South Italy). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie Suppl., 90 (2), 253 - 282." type="journal article" year="1992">
Di Sabatino et al. 
<number box="[829,892,1532,1558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Diagnostic proportions (based on measurements of two male and one female from Abe Sarabe Sefid) are: dorsal plate L/ 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" precision="555" value="-1.2">
W 
<number box="[264,316,1612,1638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.22" valueMax="1.24" valueMin="1.2">1.20</number>
</geoCoordinate>
–1.24; shoulder/frontal plate L ratio 
<number box="[759,852,1612,1638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.25" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.3</number>
; chelicera L/H 
<number box="[1041,1132,1612,1638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="6.35" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="6.2">6.2–6.5</number>
, basal segment/ claw 
<number box="[326,419,1652,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="4.3" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.1">4.1–4.5</number>
; ventral L/genital­cauda L ratio 
<number box="[797,888,1652,1678]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.9">2.9–3.1</number>
. Differences are found in a relatively shorter medial suture line of Cx­ 
<quantity box="[652,692,1692,1718]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
males, Cx­ 
<number box="[831,841,1692,1718]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
L/Cx­ 
<number box="[922,936,1692,1718]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[952,964,1692,1718]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
median L 3.0– 
<number box="[1143,1179,1692,1718]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.6">3.6</number>
(
<quantity box="[1202,1322,1692,1718]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0668" metricValueMax="1.1938" metricValueMin="0.9398" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="4.2" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.7">3.7–4.7 in</quantity>
Sicilian populations, from 
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[576,848,1732,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="8" refString="Di Sabatino, A., Gerecke, R. &amp; Cicolani, B. (1992) The water mites of the family Torrenticolidae Piersig, 1902 (Acari, Actinedida) in springs and running waters of Sicily (South Italy). Archiv fur Hydrobiologie Suppl., 90 (2), 253 - 282." type="journal article" year="1992">
Di Sabatino et al. 
<number box="[785,848,1732,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In view of the good agreement in other measurements these differences are most probably age­depending and/or due to geographical variability.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
